<div id="acknowledgments">

<h3>Acknowledgments</h3>

<p>
Surveys of the moral vegetarian literature are common. I have greatly
benefited from reading, among others, Engel 2015, Fischer 2018,
McPherson 2018, and S. Rachels 2011.</p>

<p>
I have benefited, too, from helpful comments, criticisms, and
suggestions. For them, I thank an anonymous referee, Lena Ashooh, Anne
Barnhill, Selim Berker, Mark Budolfson, Terence Cuneo, Bob Fischer,
Rachelle Gould, Matthew C. Halteman, Elizabeth Harman, Oscar Horta,
James John, Robert C. Jones, Jeff McMahan, members of the Vermont
Ethics Group, Kate Nolfi, Clare Palmer, L.A. Paul, Tina Rulli, Jeff
Sebo, Peter Singer, William O. Stephens, Sarah Stroud, Mark Timmons,
Kenny Torrella, Amy Trubek, Alisha Utter, and Daniel Vallstrom.</p>

<p>
Some material in this entry started life in Barnhill &amp; Doggett
2017a and 2017b.</p>
